class Solution {
    public int longestPalindrome(String s) {
        int[] freq = new int[128]; // ASCII range
        //0–31: Control characters (non-printable, like newline, tab); 32–126: Printable characters (letters, digits, symbols); 127: DEL (delete). So, the standard ASCII set has 128 characters total (from 0 to 127).
        int length = 0;
        boolean oddFound = false;
        for (char c : s.toCharArray()) 
            freq[c]++;
        for (int count : freq) 
        {
            length += (count / 2) * 2; 
            if (count % 2 == 1) 
                oddFound = true; 
        }
        if (oddFound) 
            length++;
        return length;
    }
}


For each character frequency:
(count / 2) * 2 → adds the largest even number ≤ count.
Example: if a character appears 5 times, we can use 4 of them (2 pairs).
If count is odd, we mark oddFound = true.
If there was at least one odd frequency, we can place one extra character in the middle of the palindrome.
Example: "abccccdd" → longest palindrome is "dccaccd" with length 7.


